//! Aliased-import construction fixture (owner module).
//!
//! Exports two DISTINCT records with divergent shapes. `Payload` carries a
//! single `code` field; `Other` carries a `tag` field AND a `note` field, so a
//! construction that conflated the two source identities would read a different
//! field set and slot count.
//!
//! An importer aliases `Payload as Tag` and constructs `Tag { … }`. Under
//! qualified-by-default the alias binding `Tag` is never opted in under the
//! source name `Payload`; the checker resolves `Tag` to the SOURCE identity
//! `aliassrc.Payload` and records that qualified name on the construction's
//! type. HIR lowering must stamp the source identity onto the StructInit result
//! type — never the bare binding `Tag` — so the MIR field-order lookup keys off
//! `aliassrc.Payload` (which strips to the registered bare `Payload`) rather
//! than the unregistered alias `Tag`, which would trip the field-order
//! fail-closed.

/// Aliased record reached through `aliassrc::{ Payload as Tag }`.
pub type Payload {
    code: i64;
}

/// A DISTINCT record sharing no layout with `Payload`. Used by the
/// no-conflation oracle: aliasing `Payload as Other` must bind the SOURCE
/// `Payload`, never this same-named `Other` export.
pub type Other {
    tag: i64;
    note: i64;
}
